In this article, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discusses various topics including Afghanistan, healthcare reform, executive pay, and financial regulatory reform. He mentions that President Obama is in the process of making a decision on troop levels in Afghanistan, and that the administration is focused on ensuring a legitimate election in Afghanistan. Gibbs also discusses the need for regulatory reform in the financial sector and the importance of a public option in healthcare reform. He mentions that the White House is evaluating legislation on revoking insurance companies' antitrust exemption and that the President is confident that healthcare reform will be achieved. Gibbs also addresses criticisms from former Vice President Dick Cheney and defends the Obama administration's approach to Afghanistan.